1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:17,000
Can Emma stay here a little?

2
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:18,933
Okay, but only for an hour.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,233
Mommy, what happened to you?

4
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:21,867
My tire broke.

5
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:24,167
And I almost got victimized
by a riding-in-tandem.

6
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:25,067
Who's that?

7
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,433
Is that Emma by the door?

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,300
Ma'am, it's me.
It's me.

9
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:30,633
Are you here to extort
money from me?

10
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,433
I should've just stolen
your wallet

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,633
if I'm after your money.

12
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,667
I even secured
all your belongings.

13
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:37,967
Why are you going to sleep
at Mookie's?

14
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,100
Let go of me!

15
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:40,400
Mookie needs me!

16
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:41,667
- Stop!
- Emma!

17
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,400
If only all your illnesses
can be transferred to me,

18
00:00:43,467 --> 00:00:45,400
so you don't have
to suffer anymore.

19
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:48,400
Mom, please don't make me cry.

20
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:51,633
Her employer doesn't let her
get near Mookie.

21
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:52,933
- Mookie!
- Do you mean

22
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,167
she's taking care of her
secretly?

23
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:34,233
Hello, Pretty Madam!

24
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:36,500
Good morning!

25
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:39,800
Oh, no!

26
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,967
It's so early to frown!

27
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:44,667
So?

28
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,667
Do you want to play cards again?

29
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:49,433
Oh, please.

30
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:50,800
Shut up.

31
00:01:56,633 --> 00:01:57,600
Who are you again?

32
00:01:58,433 --> 00:01:59,133
Oh, dear!

33
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,400
We're already close, but
you still don't know my name?

34
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:06,467
My name is Joy.

35
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:09,800
But since we are in the
Philippines, my name is Ligaya.

36
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:12,400
Call me Ligaya.

37
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:13,500
Excuse me.

38
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,467
We're not close.

39
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:20,067
And do you think I don't know
what you're doing to me?

40
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:22,067
You only want to extort
money from me.

41
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:23,067
What?

42
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:24,167
I'm not dumb.

43
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,167
I'm just letting you do that
because I'm bored.

44
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,433
That hurts.

45
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:35,167
Saying that I only want
your money is too mean.

46
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:36,400
Of course not!

47
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,767
I really want
to take care of you.

48
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,167
Fine.

49
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:41,700
We're just a little close

50
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:47,133
if you can't accept that
we're close friends.

51
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,033
Okay?

52
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:53,367
Why are you frowning?

53
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,700
I can't contact Mookie.

54
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,900
Flor isn't answering, too.

55
00:02:59,967 --> 00:03:02,933
Maybe she's sleeping or busy.

56
00:03:05,633 --> 00:03:07,467
Why don't you call Emma?

57
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:09,533
She's the one taking care
of Mookie.

58
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:14,067
What did you say?

59
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:32,667
Mookie!

60
00:03:32,733 --> 00:03:34,000
Mookie!

61
00:03:34,067 --> 00:03:35,000
Mookie!

62
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:36,633
What did you say?

63
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:39,800
Emma is taking care of Mookie?

64
00:03:39,867 --> 00:03:41,067
Oh.

65
00:03:41,133 --> 00:03:43,800
Pretty Madam is not listening.

66
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:47,233
I said call Emma.

67
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:50,533
Maybe she's with the person
taking care of Mookie.

68
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,200
That's not what you said.

69
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:55,500
Oh, no, Madam.

70
00:03:55,600 --> 00:04:00,267
Maybe your ears also got
affected by the accident.

71
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,233
You need to relax.

72
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,700
We better play cards again.

73
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:06,667
You know...

74
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:08,000
Come on.

75
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,033
My cards are new.

76
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,933
It's very crisp.

77
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:17,567
Mookie!

78
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,500
Mookie!

79
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:22,433
Mookie, wake up!

80
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,433
Mookie!

81
00:04:25,567 --> 00:04:26,667
Kayla!

82
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,267
Kayla!

83
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:32,033
Kayla, dear, wake up!

84
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:33,433
Kayla!

85
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:35,567
Dear!
Kayla!

86
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,433
Dear?

87
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,167
Dear?

88
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,233
Dear!

89
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:46,467
Thank God!

90
00:04:47,967 --> 00:04:48,900
Dear!

91
00:04:58,233 --> 00:04:59,067
Dear.

92
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:25,833
Dear, I'm sorry.

93
00:05:26,467 --> 00:05:28,167
I won't leave you again.

94
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,767
It's okay, Mother.

95
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:35,367
I've been so careless too.

96
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:39,900
Just don't do it again.

97
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:43,367
Mother...

98
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:49,200
earlier, I've heard you
calling your...

99
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:51,767
daughter.

100
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,167
Kayla.

101
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,467
You heard that?

102
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,533
You're jealous of the kid,
aren't you?

103
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:15,633
Bro?

104
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:18,433
Silly.

105
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:20,800
I'm just worried for my wife.

106
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:24,400
She can't help but be a mother.

107
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,833
She's happy with what she does
to her employer's daughter.

108
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:28,700
The kid longs for love and care.

109
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:32,533
Just support her if you don't
want your fight to get worse.

110
00:06:47,233 --> 00:06:49,967
Your mom and I wouldn't be
having this problem

111
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:53,033
if we hadn't lost you, Kayla.

112
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,967
I'll do it, Mother.

113
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:12,500
Sorry.

114
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:17,867
I remembered my daughter
when I was saving you.

115
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:20,700
You don't need to apologize.

116
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:25,733
I'll do it, Mother.

117
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,900
Can you please hand me the iPad?

118
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,600
It's my mom.

119
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,333
Hi, Mommy.

120
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:48,167
What took you so long
to answer my call?

121
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:52,367
I was in the comfort room,
Mommy?

122
00:07:52,433 --> 00:07:53,600
For an hour?

123
00:07:54,267 --> 00:07:58,033
I think I'm constipated
again, Mommy.

124
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:02,400
Remember, Mommy, you haven't
given me my injection yet.

125
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,267
You told Flor

126
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:08,800
that you would administer
my injectable meds, right?

127
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:11,167
Yes.

128
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:13,567
I'll give you a shot
when I get home.

129
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,133
Where's Flor?

130
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,200
Why can't I reach her?

131
00:08:27,033 --> 00:08:28,267
She's downstairs, Mommy.

132
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:29,767
She's cooking.

133
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:33,600
Well, call her!

134
00:08:33,667 --> 00:08:36,200
I've been calling her,
but I can't reach her!

135
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:39,700
Flor?

136
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:41,800
Flor?

137
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:47,433
Looks like she doesn't
hear me, Mommy.

138
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,733
Who are you staring at?

139
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:58,667
Is there someone else
in your room, Mookie?

140
00:08:58,733 --> 00:08:59,800
Who's there?

141
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,400
Is it Emma?

142
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:07,267
Is Emma there in your room?

143
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:08,800
She's not here, Mommy.

144
00:09:08,867 --> 00:09:10,667
Then, where's Flor?

145
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:12,933
I want to see Flor now!

146
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:18,033
Why did the screen go black?

147
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:19,700
Mookie!

148
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,067
Mookie?

149
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:28,800
Sorry, Mommy.

150
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,033
I...

151
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:34,367
I tried to get up.

152
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:38,100
Didn't I tell you not to...

153
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,767
Okay.

154
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:41,833
Okay!

155
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,333
Just get some rest!

156
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,567
Can I get it now?

157
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,667
Your mom isn't on
the line anymore.

158
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:03,400
Yes.

159
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:12,967
Are you okay?

160
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:17,133
I feel guilty about
what I'm doing.

161
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:21,367
I've been lying to mommy.

162
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:25,067
I'm sorry.

163
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:29,933
You're only doing that
to cover me and Flor.

164
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:36,967
We'll get fired once your mom
finds out about this.

165
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:40,133
Don't cry, okay?

166
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,400
I'm happy enough

167
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:03,667
that I make Mookie feel
the motherly care

168
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:05,433
she doesn't feel
from her mother.

169
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,000
I hope you understand that.

170
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:08,700
I don't understand!

171
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,333
Mookie needs me!

172
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,500
Is that the series you watch?

173
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,233
Yes, Mother. Look.

174
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:48,433
Mother?

175
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:50,567
Dear...

176
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,433
I did something wrong.

177
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:55,833
I accidentally told Pretty Madam

178
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,900
that you're looking
after Mookie.

179
00:11:58,633 --> 00:11:59,133
What?

180
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:00,933
Calm down.

181
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:03,633
I resolved it.

182
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:06,567
I used my wittiness
to get away with it.

183
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:09,267
Just trust me.

184
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:11,700
Wait. Why are you
with Ma'am Olive?

185
00:12:11,767 --> 00:12:12,733
I felt bad for her.

186
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:15,400
She's alone.

187
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,767
She has no one with her.

188
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:19,733
So I thought of looking
after her.

189
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:22,133
Mother, go home.

190
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,600
You might tell her
something else.

191
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:26,433
Just think of this...

192
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:30,400
I will be your eyes
and ears here.

193
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:33,533
I will tell you once your
employer is coming home.

194
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:37,667
Because when she finds out what
you're doing to her daughter,

195
00:12:37,733 --> 00:12:39,633
you won't just lose your job.

196
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,767
She might also send you to jail.

197
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:51,100
Dear, is it already exciting?

198
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,300
You're smiling from ear to ear.

199
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:55,833
Yes, Mother.

200
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:59,600
I still haven't gone
to an arcade.

201
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:02,800
So, every time I watch this,

202
00:13:02,867 --> 00:13:04,733
I feel like I've also been
to an arcade.

203
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,100
You haven't been to an arcade?

204
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:11,933
I've never been out of the house
all my life.

205
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:17,033
It seems like the number of days

206
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:20,267
I've been able to go out since
I was a child was just a few.

207
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,600
My mommy used to bring me

208
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:27,200
to St. Agnes Children's
Hospital.

209
00:13:27,267 --> 00:13:28,967
But she stopped doing it
eventually.

210
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:31,233
And you haven't gone outside?

211
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,967
You're just inside your house?

212
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:36,533
There was one time
that I went out.

213
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:40,767
Some girls pushed me away
in the park.

214
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:46,300
And that's also where
I heard you singing.

215
00:13:49,133 --> 00:13:55,400
It's my dream to travel.

216
00:13:58,467 --> 00:13:59,233
Mother...

217
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:02,900
can you bring me
to an arcade?

218
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:07,067
Dear, I can't.

219
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:09,767
What if your mommy finds out?

220
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,433
I'll just take a look.

221
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:17,067
I still haven't gone there.

222
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:23,933
I only want to know how it feels
to play in an arcade.

223
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:31,433
I'm sure I can never go out
once mommy is back.

224
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:09,900
Emma.

225
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:11,767
Emma.
Dan.

226
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:14,533
What are you doing here?

227
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:16,867
Emma, I'm restless.

228
00:15:18,867 --> 00:15:20,467
I want to apologize to you.

229
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:23,067
Sorry for what I said
last night.

230
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:25,833
Can we stop fighting, please?

231
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:26,967
I'm not used to it.

232
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,233
I'm also sorry for everything
I said.

233
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:44,800
Mother.

234
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,133
Mother.

235
00:15:49,633 --> 00:15:52,500
Is he Mister Danilo?

236
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,767
I'm sorry, Mookie.

237
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:55,333
Yes.

238
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,533
Danilo, this is Mookie.

239
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,100
Mookie, this is Dan.

240
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,300
- My husband.
- Hello.

241
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:02,433
Hello. Hi.

242
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,600
Hi, Mookie.

243
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:39,633
You know what, Mookie?

244
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,300
I can't understand, but...

245
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,333
Emma...

246
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,867
I feel at ease with you.

247
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:50,967
Me, too.

248
00:16:51,033 --> 00:16:51,700
Really?
Yes.

249
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,167
You two are sweet.

250
00:16:56,467 --> 00:16:57,767
See, Danilo?

251
00:16:57,833 --> 00:16:59,133
I told you.

252
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:03,333
That's why I became friends
with Mookie quickly.

253
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,200
Where are you going?

254
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:06,333
Why are you outside?

255
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,333
We're going to the arcade.

256
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,167
Arcade?
Yes.

257
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:12,833
Okay, let's go.

258
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,233
I'll bring you there.

259
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:15,600
Are you sure?
I'm sure.

260
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:17,667
I'll carry Mookie,

261
00:17:17,733 --> 00:17:18,700
then let's put her wheelchair
inside the car.

262
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:19,800
Okay.

263
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:20,733
- Come on, Mookie.
- Okay.

264
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:24,167
Thank you, Mr. Danilo.

265
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:25,900
You're welcome, Mookie.

266
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:27,767
Thank you, Dan.

267
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:33,467
Okay.
You go first.

268
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:52,867
Emma, I'll go ahead.

269
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:54,567
I still need to deliver a lot.

270
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:56,767
Okay, Dan. Thank you.

271
00:17:58,667 --> 00:17:59,267
Love you.

272
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:00,733
I love you more.

273
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,400
Bye.

274
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:05,133
Mookie, I'll go ahead.

275
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:07,200
- Be safe.
- Have fun.

276
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:08,067
Be safe.
Be safe.

277
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:09,833
- Bye, Emma.
- Be safe, too.

278
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:13,933
You're two are so sweet, Mother.

279
00:18:15,033 --> 00:18:17,200
My husband is really sweet.

280
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:19,033
I'm lucky to have a caring,

281
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,467
kind, and sweet husband
like him.

282
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:26,067
I hope I also meet someone
like Mister Danilo.

283
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:29,400
Someone who will love
and care for me.

284
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:35,200
There is someone meant
for each of us.

285
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,567
There's a special
someone for you.

286
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:39,633
Someone is meant for you.

287
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:46,600
But I think it's impossible,
Mother.

288
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:49,800
I might only become
a burden to him.

289
00:18:49,867 --> 00:18:53,367
I'm sure, someone who will
love you will come along.

290
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:55,800
Let's go.

291
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:56,967
Let's have fun.

292
00:18:57,033 --> 00:18:57,533
Come on!
Okay.

293
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:04,267
Wait.

294
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:05,767
Okay.

295
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:09,767
Mother.
Emma, dear.

296
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:14,400
Can you go home for now?

297
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:17,767
Kutsy will give me money.

298
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:20,933
Mookie and I are in the mall.

299
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:21,533
What?

300
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,700
You're so stupid!

301
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:26,533
You're not using your brain,
Emma.

302
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:29,267
You'll be in trouble if your
employer finds out about it.

303
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:31,133
She won't be home
until tomorrow.

304
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:32,633
Oh, no.

305
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:33,833
I shouldn't have told you.

306
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,567
You might have another slip
of the tongue.

307
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:38,033
No, I won't do that again.

308
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:41,167
But bring that kid home.

309
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,333
Bye, Mother. Let's talk later.

310
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,100
I'm telling you, Emma.

311
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:46,400
Emma.

312
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:48,233
Emma!

313
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:49,333
Let's go.

314
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,600
Mookie!

315
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,500
Where do you want to go?

316
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:13,933
Where?

317
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:14,767
There?
Okay.

318
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:30,567
Mookie!

319
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:32,567
Mookie!

320
00:20:33,467 --> 00:20:35,200
You left me!

321
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,100
Can you still do it, Madam?

322
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:12,700
What?

323
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:14,267
Ace?

324
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,833
And a diamond ace?

325
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:18,733
You're going to lose again.

326
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:21,600
Remember, you've already
owed me five thousand pesos

327
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:23,500
since yesterday.

328
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,933
It's all in my mind.

329
00:21:28,867 --> 00:21:29,967
I'm just joking.

330
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:31,833
Go on.

331
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:35,733
I'm done.

332
00:21:37,433 --> 00:21:39,200
Can you call the nurse?

333
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:40,167
I need to pee.

334
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:41,533
Pee?

335
00:21:42,533 --> 00:21:43,567
Urinate?

336
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:46,000
Why do we have to bother
the nurse?

337
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:48,200
I'll assist you.

338
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:48,900
Come on.

339
00:21:48,967 --> 00:21:50,367
I can do it.

340
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:54,033
Here's your slippers.

341
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,133
Come on.

342
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:58,433
There.

343
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:09,333
Hold on to me, Madam.

344
00:22:20,733 --> 00:22:21,433
Look over there.

345
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:28,867
Mookie, aren't you tired yet?

346
00:22:28,933 --> 00:22:30,933
We've been walking around.

347
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:33,467
Mom, don't worry.

348
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:35,400
I'm not tired.

349
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:39,300
Actually, I don't feel
anything unusual.

350
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:42,467
If I'm not in a wheelchair,

351
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:44,300
I think I will forget
that I'm sick.

352
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:49,967
There.

353
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:51,767
Slowly.

354
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:54,367
I'll put it here.

355
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:56,200
There, okay.

356
00:22:56,267 --> 00:22:57,167
Wait. Wait.

357
00:22:58,700 --> 00:22:59,900
Where are you going?

358
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:01,833
I'll go with you.

359
00:23:02,867 --> 00:23:05,467
You might get dizzy and fall.

360
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:06,767
I will catch you.

361
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:08,867
Let's go.

362
00:23:10,733 --> 00:23:11,500
It's okay.

363
00:23:12,133 --> 00:23:13,067
I can manage.

364
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,667
Thank you.

365
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,433
I can do this.
Thank you.

366
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:20,967
You're welcome.

367
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:32,800
The witch thanked me.

368
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,667
She was even smiling.

369
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,667
So, this is how it feels
to be in the arcade.

370
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:44,433
There's a lot of people.

371
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,867
It's so fun.

372
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,367
I feel like a normal girl.

373
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:58,200
So, this is how it feels
to be normal.

374
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,267
I'm sorry, Dear.

375
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:04,233
I don't have money.

376
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:06,200
You can't try the rides.

377
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:08,467
It's okay, Mother.

378
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:10,367
It's all good.

379
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:16,867
Actually, you being here
with me...

380
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,800
means a lot to me.

381
00:24:25,233 --> 00:24:26,933
I want to take a picture.

382
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,100
But...

383
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,700
mommy might see it on my tablet.

384
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,867
I have a cell phone.

385
00:24:34,933 --> 00:24:37,333
But the camera isn't that good.

386
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:38,767
It's okay.

387
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:39,800
Would that be fine?

388
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:40,467
Okay.

389
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:08,667
Here.

390
00:25:08,733 --> 00:25:12,100
Something to remind you of your
first time being in a mall.

391
00:25:12,167 --> 00:25:13,100
Thank you.

392
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:14,833
OMG!

393
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:16,633
Zayn is here, too.

394
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:20,000
Why is he with a weirdo?

395
00:25:20,067 --> 00:25:20,767
Is it good?

396
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:22,733
Pistachio is their bestseller.

397
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,433
- What's happening to you?
- Mother.

398
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,533
I'm allergic to pistachio.

399
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,333
Help!

400
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,533
Help!

401
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:31,600
I suggest you discuss this
incident with her doctor.

402
00:25:31,667 --> 00:25:34,833
Because I don't think
she's allergic to pistachio.

403
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:38,000
Does it mean mommy's diagnosis
was wrong?

404
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:38,700
Sir.

405
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:41,000
Where's the patient?

406
00:25:41,067 --> 00:25:42,400
She's been discharged.

407
00:25:42,467 --> 00:25:43,633
Ma'am Olive!

408
00:25:44,867 --> 00:25:48,333
Emma, I'm begging you.
Answer my call.
